  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "It would be excellent if we can pass in an array of directories that will output the types directory to several locations at one go\r\n\r\nThis way, we can use the types easily inside our front end and back end (meaning blockchain dev) even though the front end and back end are in 2 separate folders and when new types are generated, it will be update both folders\r\n\r\nI have done a demo that uses hardhat, typechain and added a front end (github repo)[https://github.com/myhendry/OPEN]. If types generated can be outputted to various directories, it will be available on both front and back end and makes type checking easier\r\n\r\n\r\n",
